Stapes, incus and maleus (middle ear bones) are not responsible for your balance.
There are two broad components that regulate our balance:
First, the 3 semicircular canals, saccule and utricle give us sense of acceleration. Second, our cerebellum and nerve endings on our muscles as well as joint ligaments regulate our sense of position (proprioception). Both of this components work together to prevent us from falling over when there is a strong wind pushing us or when we are climbing down stairs.
